title: Top travel photos of the week
text:
Top travel photos of the week Last updated 10:47, September 25 2015 JIM YOUNG/Reuters Scott Barbour/RETERS Johannes Simon/Getty Images MARK MAKELA/REUTERS MICHAELA REHLE/REUTERS ILYA NAYMUSHIN/REUTERS KIM KYUNG-HOON/REUTERS GUILLERMO GRANJA/REUTERS WONG CAMPION/REUTERS Robertus Pudyanto/GETTY IMAGES EDGAR SU/REUTERS ChinaFotoPress/GETTY IMAGES MARIANA BAZO/REUTERS Robertus Pudyanto/GETTY IMAGES Darren Staples/REUTERS 
Western lowland gorilla Kamba licks her one-day-old son Zachary at the Brookfield Zoo in Brookfield, Illinois, United States. 
Mini dachshunds Willy (C), dressed as a surf livesaver and Cooper (R), dressed as a racing car driver compete in the Hophaus Southgate Inaugural Best Dressed Dachshund competition. 
A young woman drinks beer at Hofbraeuhaus beer tent on the opening day of the 2015 Oktoberfest. The 182nd Oktoberfest will be open to the public from September 19 through October 4 and will draw millions of visitors from across the globe in the world's largest beer fest 
Pope Francis figurines are seen on a window display in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. Pope Francis travels to Philadelphia in his six-day visit to the United States. 
A visitor drinks beer on the first day of the 182nd Oktoberfest in Munich, Germany. Millions of beer drinkers from around the world will come to the Bavarian capital over the next two weeks for Oktoberfest. 
Local skateboarder Markel Andronov jumps over an art work by a German street artist who goes by the name "Evol", in central Krasnoyarsk, Siberia, Russia. 
Participants run past the Tiananmen gate, with a portrait of China's late leader Mao Zedong hanging on it, during the Beijing International Marathon in Beijing, China, September. About 30,000 runners participated in the annual running event. 
The Cotopaxi volcano, one of the world's highest active volcanoes, spews smoke as seen from Quito, Ecuador. Ecuadorian authorities are monitoring activity at Cotopaxi volcano, which prompted Ecuador's President Rafael Correa to declare a state of emergency and authorities to maintain a yellow alert for eruptions as bursts of ash keep spewing from the snow-encircled crater of the volcano and falling in gusts on residential communities. 
A boy poses for a photograph with a tiger behind a glass wall in Yunnan Wildlife Park in Kunming, Yunnan province, China. 
Indonesian Muslims attend to Eid Al-Adha prayer in Surabaya, Indonesia. Muslims worldwide celebrate Eid Al-Adha, to commemorate the Prophet Ibrahim's readiness to sacrifice his son as a sign of his obedience to God, during which they sacrifice permissible animals, generally goats, sheep, and cows. 
Tourists take photos with the landmarks of the central business district shrouded by haze at Merlion Park in Singapore. 
Tourists walk on a suspension bridge made of glass at the Shiniuzhai National Geological Park in Pingjiang County, China. The 300-meter-long glass suspension bridge, with a maximum height of 180 meters, opened to the public on Thursday. 
Japanese tourist pose for a photo with Peruvian anti-riot police in Lima's main square in down town Lima. 
Vietnamese devotees gather to see buffalo fighting festival at Do Son stadium in Do Son, Vietnam. Vietnamese devotees have held the buffalo fighting festival annually since the 18th century to honour The God of Water and to pray for safety, prosperity, and good harvest. The Festival, which attracts both local people and international tourists, also expresses the martial spirit of people in the village of Do Son. Thirty-two buffalos fight in final round today for prize 70 millions Vietnam Dong. 
All Blacks fan pose for a photo outside Wembley Stadium before the All Blacks took on Argentina in their Rugby World Cup opener in London. 1 of 15 
Here is our round up of the top travel photos from around the world. 
Do you have a favourite? Let us know in the comments.
